          "id": 334,
          "title": "The major parties could take the fight to One Nation on health, housing and the economy \u2013 but will they? | Tom McIlroy",
          "body": "<p>Ahead of the Farrer byelection, a return to issues that are fundamental to Australians could help stall Hanson\u2019s rise</p><ul><li><p>Get our <a href=\"https://www.theguardian.com/email-newsletters?CMP=cvau_sfl\">breaking news email</a>, <a href=\"https://app.adjust.com/w4u7jx3\">free app</a> or <a href=\"https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/series/full-story?CMP=cvau_sfl\">daily news podcast</a></p></li></ul><p>Albury hospital is in a critical condition.</p><p>Serving 300,000 people in the communities of Albury-Wodonga, Beechworth, Wangaratta and surrounding towns, the hospital is the subject of a controversial $558m redevelopment, and has been dogged by \u201cescalating unrest\u201d among staff.</p> <a href=\"https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2026/mar/28/farrer-byelection-one-nation-health-housing-economy-pauline-hanson-ntwnfb\">Continue reading...</a>",
